title: Arizona Coyotes confidential with Klas Dahlbeck
text:
Klas Dahlbeck
Position: Defense.
Age: 24.
Last season
Dahlbeck started the season with the Blackhawks organization, tallying one goal in four NHL games. He spent the majority of his time in the American Hockey League before the highly-touted defensive prospect was traded to the Coyotes in February for center Antoine Vermette. In 19 games with the Coyotes, Dahlbeck added three assists.
AZCENTRAL
Arizona Coyotes XTRA app: Get latest news, scores
2015-16 outlook
After splitting time between the NHL and AHL last season, Dahlbeck is on the brink of a full-time role with the Coyotes. He has a spot in the top-six and will be counted on as a vital component of the team’s contingent of young talent. Look for him to showcase a hard-to-play-against style that specializes in the defensive details.
Camp focus
It appears Dahlbeck will start the season next to Zbynek Michalek. The two skated together in camp and could develop into a solid shutdown pair for the Coyotes. But Dahlbeck also wants to be able to help the team transition into the offensive zone.
“I want to be a good solid defender and help make good passes out of the zone and just follow up on the play,” Dahlbeck said.

Quick hits
-Best road city: Vancouver.
-Pregame meal: Chicken and rice.
-Favorite app: Facebook.
-First car: Volkswagen Golf.
-Can’t-miss TV show: Narcos.
